719868f-a.text:
Fort Washington Park: A northerly view from a point on a line with West 178th Street, showing the northern half of this North River marginal park. Paralleling the water's edge are the New York Central Railroad tracks. The photographer's vantage point is a small pedestrian bridge across this chasm. Views 2 and 3 are similar, several years
later.
1923.
Views 2 & 3: May 27, 1927.
L. Sperr.
719868f-a.folder: 178th Street & St. Nicholas Avenue, Manhattan, NY

723158f-a.text:
St. Nicholas Avenue (formerly Eleventh Avenue), north from 178th Street. This section has grown up almost entirely since 1914,
and especially since the World War.
May 27, 1927.
P. L. Sperr.
